00:05:15.360 --> 00:05:22.360
So there are other options associated with
that is there are a lot of people who try

00:05:23.120 --> 00:05:27.539
to run some chemicals for example sea foam
and things like that. We dont have any

00:05:27.539 --> 00:05:33.830
claims that we know for certain that that
works. That is something that could potentially

00:05:33.830 --> 00:05:39.870
prevent it and also again just a disclaimer
a catch can will not solve your problem. It

00:05:39.870 --> 00:05:43.030
doesnt mean you will never have carbon
build up. What that means is that it will

00:05:43.030 --> 00:05:47.060
help slow down the process and so you will
catch a lot more of those contaminants before

00:05:47.060 --> 00:05:52.009
they get into your engine and get re-burned.
Some stuff is still going to get in there

00:05:52.009 --> 00:05:57.500
and you are still going to end up with carbon
it might last you another 10, 20, 30,000 miles.

00:05:57.500 --> 00:06:03.840
Other options associated with that stuff is
manufactures are starting to test with additional

00:06:03.840 --> 00:06:08.819
fuel injectors. Some of them like Toyota are
starting to put injectors in every single

00:06:08.819 --> 00:06:13.860
cylinder. So on a 4 cylinder engine you might
have 8 fuel injectors; 4 in the cylinder,

00:06:13.860 --> 00:06:20.189
4 in the intake track. Some people are testing
with throttle by injectors. This way again

00:06:20.189 --> 00:06:25.599
we are getting fuel one those valves keeping
them clean. In the end at this point there

00:06:25.599 --> 00:06:30.379
is no perfect solution for this problem and
all you are trying to do is prevent it as

00:06:30.379 --> 00:06:36.270
much as you possibly can.
